NUMBER 3304 
NAME In the Mists
REGION 15
CHANNEL 72
ASTRAL
EXIT S 3301
EXIT N 3307
MONSTER_GROUP 45
*DESCRIPTION_START
Vague shapes barely discernible through the thick mist suggest trees hung 
with heavy moss. From the south, occasional bright flares of light cast 
luminous shadows in a rainbow of colors. To the north, the mist darkens 
ominously.
*DESCRIPTION_END
MONSTER_GROUP 45
CALL 19      
ITEM 0 229
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 0
Dark against the mist, the shapes raise spindly limbs to what would be sky if 
there were sky in this place. Thick moss drapes over branches and hangs 
nearly to the ground, reminding you of mages' robes.
*DESCRIPTION_END
IFVERB RECALL -1
  ECHO PLAYER An old tale tickles your subconscious, bringing the trees to your attention.
ENDIF
IFVERB RECALL 0
  IFVAR SKILL32 > 0
    ECHO PLAYER You vaguely recall a tale of mages set to guard a path.
    ECHO OTHERS %n frowns slightly as if something eludes %h grasp.
  ENDIF
  IFVAR SKILL32 > 5
    ECHO PLAYER Casting about in your memory, you recall a few more details.
    ECHO PLAYER The mages were transformed into trees by an order of dark mages. 
    ECHO OTHERS %S furrows %h brow in concentration.
  ENDIF
  IFVAR SKILL32 > 10
    ECHO PLAYER Concentrating further on the shapes, you pull a name from their vague unease...
    ECHO PLAYER ...The Left Hand of Chaos.          
    ECHO OTHERS After a moment, %s closes %h eyes, concentrating more deeply.
  ENDIF
  IFVAR SKILL32 > 20
    ECHO PLAYER Increasing your concentration, you draw out the name of those the trees guard against...
    ECHO PLAYER ...The Order of the White Rose.                              
    ECHO OTHERS %S slips into a light trance, %h face going completely blank.
    ECHO OTHERS %S murmurs something softly, then repeats it more loudly.
    ECHO OTHERS %n says, "The Order of the White Rose."
  ENDIF
ENDIF
  
