ITEM 0 773 VAL2=3318
ITEM 1 81 VAL2=3323

;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
;arrive through opening from room 3303, the broom closet
NUMBER 3322 
NAME Storage Room 
REGION 15
CHANNEL 72  
ASTRAL
PARTIAL_DARKNESS
;
*DESCRIPTION_START
Somewhere at the edges of your perception, you sense a dank horror made up of 
more than just the stench of wet rot and the sounds of something scuttling in 
the corners. Dimly seen shapes are stacked along the walls, and piled 
haphazardly around the floor, leaving only a narrow path between them.
*DESCRIPTION_END                                       
;
CALL 19
;
ITEM 0 74 VAL2=3323
ITEM 1 641
;
IFENTRY
  GENMON 27
  GENMON 27
  GENMON 1
  GENMON 20
ENDIF
IFVERB SEARCH -1
  ECHO PLAYER Your search disturbs a nest of insects, but you do find a lever on the wall.
  ECHO OTHERS %n pokes among the boxes, disturbing a nest of insects.
  SPELL 522
ENDIF
;
IFPREVERB GO 0
  CLEARVERB
  DISBAND
  ECHO PLAYER You slowly make your way through the narrow path, brushing against objects that squirm oddly out of your way.
  EQUAL ROUNDTIME 10
  ECHO PLAYER [Round: 10 sec]
  PLREVENT 3
  CONTPLREVENT
  MOVE 3323
  SHOWROOM 3323
  AFFECT 3323
  ECHO OTHERS %n emerges from between two stacks of boxes.
ENDIF
IFPREVERB PULL 1
  IFNOITEM 2
    ECHO PLAYER As you pull the lever, a section of wall slides into a recessed pocket, revealing an opening.
    ECHO OTHERS %n pulls a lever, and a section of wall slides into a recessed pocket, revealing an opening.
    NEWITEM 2 72 VAL2=3303                                    
    AFFECT 3303 
    NEWITEM 3 72 VAL2=3322
    ECHO ALL The shelves glide silently into a recessed pocket, revealing an opening.
    AFFECT 3322
  ENDIF
ENDIF
IFPREVERB PUSH 1
  IFITEM 2
    ECHO PLAYER You push the lever down, and a section of wall slides over the opening.
    ECHO OTHERS %n pushes the lever, and a section of wall slides over the opening.
    REMOVEITEM 2
    AFFECT 3303
    REMOVEITEM 3
    ECHO ALL The shelves glide silently closed over the opening.
  ENDIF
ENDIF    
;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
NUMBER 3323 
NAME Misty Stairs, Basement Level
REGION 15
CHANNEL 72                  
ASTRAL
MONSTER_GROUP 45
EXIT O 3322
ITEM 0 81 VAL2=3321
CALL 19
;
*DESCRIPTION_START
A semi-solid stairway rises from the mist as if carved from it, its upper 
steps shrouded in a wreath of brilliant, pulsing light. A burnished gold 
railing spirals along beside the stair, with no visible means of support. 
Outside the circle of light cast from above, the mist shimmers and changes 
color constantly with no seeming pattern to it.
*DESCRIPTION_END
IFPREVERB CLIMB 0
  IFVAR FLAG1 ! 1
    CLEARVERB
    ECHO PLAYER As you step toward the stairs, a figure forms from the mist and bars your way.
    IFNOITEM 1
      NEWITEM 1 639 ADJ1=197
    ENDIF
    ECHO ALL The figure shimmers slightly and you sense in your mind that it seeks a password.
  ENDIF
ENDIF
IFTOUCH 1
  CLEARVERB
  ECHO PLAYER The mist thins slightly and the figure reforms, unaffected by your touch.
ENDIF
IFPREVERB LISTEN 1
  CLEARVERB
  ECHO PLAYER You sense in your mind that the password is the symbol of the Left Hand's ancient enemies.
  ECHO OTHERS The figure turns toward %n.
ENDIF
IFSAY white_rose
  ECHO PLAYER The figure nods slightly to you and steps aside to let you pass.
  ECHO OTHERS The figure nods slightly to %n and steps aside.
  EQUAL FLAG1 1
ENDIF
IFSAY a_white_rose
  ECHO PLAYER The figure nods slightly to you and steps aside to let you pass.
  ECHO OTHERS The figure nods slightly to %n and steps aside.
  EQUAL FLAG1 1
ENDIF
IFSAY white_rose?
  ECHO PLAYER The figure nods slightly to you and steps aside to let you pass.
  ECHO OTHERS The figure nods slightly to %n and steps aside.
  EQUAL FLAG1 1
ENDIF
;
